The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP),  on Sunday announced the suspension of \Prince Kassim Afegbua of ward 5, Etsako East Local government area of Edo State. The State PDP declarwed that Afegbua has been Suspended for a period of one month with effect from August 2, 2020 by the ward executive after being found guilty of anti-party activities.
The State Chairman, Hon Tony Aziegbemi, has directed the local government chairman to set up a disciplinary committee to investigate the allegations of anti-party activities levied against him.
The EDO PDP State Publicity Secretary, Chris Osa Nehikhare, in a statement on Sunday indicted that the composition of the disciplinary committee will be announced in due course.